      "detail": "All eight citizen archetypes involve cognitive harms: misinformation, fraud, bias, IP theft, harmful content. No archetype involves robotic or physical-world AI. The bill's regulatory principles — transparency, fairness, contestability — are cognitive-domain governance tools. Physical-world AI regulation would require different mechanisms that the bill does not address."
    },
    "Role": {
      "value": "Copilot/worker",
      "memo": "Holmes's bill governs AI doing consequential work within organisations, not merely assisting human thought.",
      "detail": "The AI Responsible Officer requirement presumes AI systems have enough role authority to make consequential decisions: screening applicants, processing claims, generating commercial content. An assistant role would not need a designated corporate officer. The bill's accountability framework is calibrated for AI that does work, not AI that merely advises. The copilot framing captures the bounded-but-consequential role the bill regulates."
    },
    "Actuation": {
      "value": "Informational",
      "memo": "Holmes's harm channels flow through information: misinformation, biased decisions, IP theft, and manipulative content.",
