    },
    "Autonomy": {
      "value": "Human-in-loop",
      "memo": "Holmes's statutory principles of accountability, contestability, and the AI Responsible Officer mandate human approval before consequential AI action.",
      "detail": "The bill's governance architecture requires human oversight at multiple points: the AI Responsible Officer ensures ethical deployment, contestability and redress preserve challenge rights, and transparency mandates require human-readable disclosure. This is human-in-loop governance: consequential actions require human-accountable decision points. The bill's strength relative to the UK status quo is precisely this shift from on-loop to in-loop."
    },
    "Delegated Authority": {
